description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an Employment Retention Worker to expand out Employment Retention Service. You will join a small team of specialist advisors that will support individuals with severe and enduring mental health problems to retain their employment if they are off sick or at risk of losing their job.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will manage your own caseload of clients and support them and their employers to resolve any issues, look at sustainable return to work plans, and offer advice on reasonable adjustments to the workplace that can enable our clients to remain at work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive regular supervision and support from the team and will be part of the wider Employment Service. Ideally the successful candidate will have previous experience of supporting people with mental health problems or disabilities to retain their employment. Training and support will be provided to the successful candidate as will a full induction into the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about the role please contact Doreen Till on doreen.till@nhs.net or Vicky Harris on vicky.harris@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that the banding for this role is subject to confirmation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameVicky HarrisJob titleEmployment and Recovery Programme ManagerEmail addressvicky.harris7@nhs.netTelephone number07584 602273&lt;/p&gt;
